<br>
Early on, the controlled destruction line is extremely effective. When I first made my MA (primary), they were practically useless. I remember when I first used Crash of Thunder. Nano shutdown was hella long and about got me killed. In contrast, after the fix my nano-MA (secondary MA) would crush everything in her level teen-twenty path with it. <br>
<br>
Main problem with them later on is that they don't scale particularily well. When you're hitting for 1200, +57 isn't all that. It helps, but it's not a huge increase in damage output. It's useful on mobs that have to die as quickly as possible, but the tradeoff is the nano cost. If you have a small nano pool, they might not be worth using if it costs you 1/4 to 1/3 of your nano. You'd most likely be better off just using your heals.  <br>
<br>
You'll get them regardless if you're spending IP for heals (hint hint), so it's up to you which ones to use or even bother to buy/look for. <br>
